-- Hungary Receives Nuclear Plant Bid From Rosatom, Portfolio Says
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-06-06T06:16:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/hungary-receives-nuclear-plant-bid-from-rosatom-portfolio-says.html
Hungary  received a bid for the
planned expansion of the Paks nuclear plant from Russia’s state-
run nuclear holding company Rosatom Corp., news website
 Portfolio  said, citing Pal Kovacs, state secretary at the
Development Ministry.  Hungary, which plans to build two additional blocks in
Paks, expects to get at least five bids, Istvan Hamvas, the
plant’s chief executive officer said, according to Portfolio.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  